This paper deals with privacy concerns in collecting and analyzing data from smart device users, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a system for performing complex machine learning tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical aspects of local differential privacy, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and cryptography and security (cs.CY).
